**Segments**

- **Product Type**: The gluten-free products market can be segmented by product type into bakery products, snacks & ready-to-eat meals, pasta & rice, and others. Bakery products, including bread, cakes, and cookies, dominate this segment due to the high demand for gluten-free alternatives in this category. Snacks and ready-to-eat meals are also gaining traction as convenient options for consumers with gluten sensitivities.

- **Distribution Channel**: In terms of distribution channels, the market can be segmented into supermarkets/hypermarkets, specialty stores, online retail, and others. Supermarkets/hypermarkets hold a significant share in distributing gluten-free products due to their wide reach and accessibility. Specialty stores cater to niche markets looking for specific gluten-free offerings, while online retail is experiencing rapid growth fueled by e-commerce trends.

- **End-User**: The end-user segment includes segments such as households, food service industry, and food manufacturers. Households represent a major consumer base for gluten-free products as individuals seek healthier alternatives. The food service industry, including restaurants and cafes, has also been incorporating gluten-free options into their menus to cater to a broader customer base. Food manufacturers play a crucial role in producing and innovating gluten-free products to meet the growing demand.

